  <h2>Base64 Encoder / Decoder</h2>
  <p>
    Base64 is a group of binary-to-text encoding schemes that represent binary data in an ASCII string format by translating it into a radix-64 representation.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Encode</strong> text or files into Base64 strings.</li>
    <li><strong>Decode</strong> Base64 strings back into human-readable text or download as files.</li>
    <li><strong>Live mode</strong> to instantly see changes as you type.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Common Use Cases</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Embedding image data directly into HTML or CSS (<code>data:image/png;base64,...</code>).</li>
    <li>Transferring data over media that are designed to deal with textual data (like JSON or XML).</li>
    <li>Basic data obfuscation (Note: Base64 is <strong>not</strong> encryption).</li>
  </ul>
